A second female employee of popular Soweto restaurant Moja Cafe has come out with claims that she was also strip- searched after being accused of stealing a cellphone. Head chef Nosipho Radebe could not hold back her tears when she related a story of how a female supervisor and a female off-duty colleague whose phone was misplaced, ordered her to take off her clothes so they could search her. Radebe, 31, opened up about the alleged abuse at the hands of her employers after our sister publication Sowetan reported this week about a similar incident involving one of the restaurant's waitresses, Nikita Ntshingila. TO READ MORE ON THIS STORY GET A COPY OF TODAY'S SUNDAY WORLD.